The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions the use of benchmark datasets, which suggests that it falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of different models, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of the current models, which suggests that it falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
